{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When hemorrhoids first strike, you will probably run straight to a medical professional. The doctor will give you an examination and some advice for treatments. Hoever, you should not require prescribed medicines. You can use the tips in this article to handle hemorrhoids on your own, rather than through the doctor.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Avoid caffeine and alcohol because they are diuretics and cause dehydration. Avoid hot, spicy foods because they cause direct irritation. Both of these effects can aggravate your symptoms. In fact, eating spicy foods can inflame hemorrhoids to a point of painful burning, so steer clear of them if you don&#39;t want to spend all your time in the bathroom.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/portrait-of-high-fiber-foods.png\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"portrait of high fiber foods\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/>If you have to exert yourself too much to have a bowel movement, you can cause yourself hemorrhoids. Changes to your diet that can make your bowel movements easier include taking in more water, eating more fiber, and eating fewer refined foods.&nbsp;If you increase your fiber intake, you will avoid constipation and hard stools, both of which contribute to hemorrhoid problems, and it can help your hemorrhoids heal and prevent future flare-ups.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A hemorrhoid that bleeds into your stool is quite common and is no cause for panic. When your stools are very firm, they may irritate the hemorrhoid and cause it to bleed. Add <a href=\"http:\/\/www.webmd.com\/diet\/6-foods-and-tips-for-more-fiber\"  >more fibers to your diet<\/a> or find a supplement you can take to make your stools softer. While hemorrhoids are most likely the cause of blood in your stool, check with your doctor to make sure, as it may also indicate a more troubling condition, such as rectal cancer. Get your condition diagnosed by a doctor so you can stop worrying. If it is hemorrhoids, your doctor will recommend&nbsp;the <a href=\"http:\/\/hemclear.com\/\"  >best course of treatment<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When going to the bathroom, a squatting position can help to avoid excessive straining. Prop up your feet on a stool while you use the bathroom. In places where people squat instead of sitting down for bowel movements, hemorrhoids are uncommon.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You should now know how to prevent the formation of hemorrhoids and how to properly treat them if they do occur. With proper care and&nbsp;an improved diet, you can treat your hemorrhoids at home, and even <a href=\"advice-for-preventing-and-treating-your-hemorrhoids\"  >prevent hemorrhoids<\/a> from ever being a problem again.<\/p>\r\n"}